"faqAnswer1" = "It is a secure, multi-authentication wallet based on MPC technology that is used to manage digital assets. Transactions require approval from multiple devices.";
"faqAnswer2" = "Vultisig offers enhanced security with multi-device authentication, support for many blockchains, easy recovery options, and no seed phrases or user tracking.";
"faqAnswer3" = "Yes, as long as you saved and have access to your backups when creating the vault. You can import these backups on a new device to regain access to your assets.";
"faqAnswer4" = "Vultisig securely stores and manages digital assets. All actions, such as sending or swapping, require the threshold of devices to sign transactions.";
"faqAnswer5" = "Vultisig is free to use. Only standard network fees apply to sending. And for swaps and bridges, there's a 0.5% (50 bps) fee.";
"faqAnswer6" = "Vultisig supports major cryptocurrencies and tokens, with over 30 chains and their tokens, currently available.";
"faqAnswer7" = "Yes, Vultisig is open source and has undergone security audits. Both the audit reports and the source code are accessible.";
"faqAnswer8" = "Vultisig does not store any user information from its mobile apps.";
"faqAnswer9" = "It is built on MPC technology, which eliminates the need for seed phrases and supports multiple blockchains, making Vultisig flexible and chain-agnostic.";
